<TITLE> Maharashtra CM offers to resign </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 NEW DELHI, Dec 01(bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Maharashtra chief minister Vilasrao Deshmukh, a member of the ruling Congress party, said on Monday he had offered to resign over the attacks in Mumbai that killed 183 people. "I have offered to resign," Deshmukh told reporters, adding he was waiting for party leaders to make a final decision.
